com.fujitsu.xml.xlink.dataset
Interface Locator

public interface Locator

Interface that provides locator information.
Locator information is obtained from link declaration information.

Method Detail

getParent

public XLinkDeclaration getParent()
Link declaration information to which locator information belongs is obtained.
Returns:
The link declaration information is returned.

getDefinition

public Node getDefinition()
The node with which the locator information is defined is obtained.
Returns:
The node with which the locator information is defined is returned.

getType

public short getType()
The element type of the node with which the locator information is defined is obtained.
Locator information indicates the model of the locator type element or resource type element that is defined with XLink. This method returns a constant indicating an element type.
Returns:
Either of the following constants is returned:
  • Locator.TYPE_LOCATOR (When element type "locator" is defined with XLink)
  • Locator.TYPE_RESOURCE (When element type "resource" is defined with XLink)

getHref

public Address getHref()
Address information is obtained.
Address information indicates the class with which the href attribute value of a locator type element is analyzed and held.
Returns:
The address information is returned.
Null is returned in one of the following cases:
  • The locator information is created from a node of element type "resource".
    In this case, a start source of a simple type element is contained.
  • No href attribute value is defined with the locator type element from which the locator information is created.
  • An incorrect href attribute value is defined with the locator type element from which the locator information is created.

getRole

public java.lang.String getRole()
The role attribute value is obtained.
Returns:
The role attribute value is returned.
If no role attribute value is defined, a empty string is returned.

getTitle

public java.lang.String getTitle()
The title attribute value is obtained.
Returns:
The title attribute value is returned.
If no title attribute value is defined, a empty string is returned.

getLabel

public java.lang.String getLabel()
The label attribute value is obtained.
The label attribute value is used when locator information is specified using arc information.
Returns:
The label attribute value is returned.
If no label attribute value is defined, a empty string is returned.

getTitleList

public TitleList getTitleList()
The title information list is obtained.
The title information list held in the locator information is returned.
Title information held in a title information list is information about a title type element that is a child element of a locator type element or resource type element.
Returns:
The title information list is returned.
If no corresponding title information is present, a empty list is returned.

getResources

public NodeSet getResources()
The target resource is obtained.
The target resource is returned as a node set.
As shown below, a node is held in the node set in accordance with the element type of the node from which the locator information is created.
  • For the resource type
    Node from which the locator information is created
  • For the locator type
    Node obtained as an address information analysis result
When locator information is created from an element of either of the two types below, the node held in a returned node set is the element.
  • Resource
  • Simple
The method below is supported to check a node to see if it is under the control of a resource type element or simple type element.
  • XLinkProcessor.hasStartingResourceAncestor(Node)
Returns:
The node set holding the resource is returned.
